{
  "texts": [
    "For the temporal affine augmentations, flipping the frames also slightly improved the performance.",
    "Surprisingly, temporal scaling seemed to have negative effects on the model performance.",
    "This may be due to poor choice of the range of temporal scaling factors (see Section 3.3), where the pupil movement patterns became too unnatural.From Table 3, we see that the event processing choices had very little impact on accuracy, but our benchmark (with causal event volume binning) ensures causality in the model as described in 3.1.1.",
    "For architectural choices, we see that using a CenterNet like head led to a boost of 0.027, compared with the \"no detector\" (a simpler head with global average pooling and 2 dense layers).",
    "Similarly, using a larger temporal kernel led to a small boost in p10 accuracy (0.008) at a small computation cost (8.3M MACs)."
  ]
}